âœ… 2) MongoDB (Mongoose) Schemas â€” simplified (fields + explanation) User User { _id, name: String, phone: String, // unique role: "user" | "provider" | "admin", addresses: [{label, line1, city, pincode, location:{lat,lng}}], avatarUrl, createdAt, updatedAt, verified: Boolean }

Provider Provider { _id, userRef: ObjectId, // reference to User categories: [String], // e.g., ["Plumber","AC"] services: [{ title, description, basePrice, priceRange, durationMins }], documents: [{ type: "Aadhar"|"PAN"|"DL", fileUrl, status: "pending"|"approved"|"rejected" }], location: { lat, lng, areaCode, city }, availability: { online: Boolean, schedule: [...] }, rating: { avg: Number, count: Number }, earnings: Number, createdAt, updatedAt }

Booking Booking { _id, userId, providerId (nullable until assigned), category, serviceDetail, description, photos: [url], videoUrl, address, location:{lat,lng}, preferredDateTime, status: "requested"|"assigned"|"accepted"|"in_progress"|"completed"|"cancelled", priceQuoted, paymentMode: "COD"|"Online", createdAt, updatedAt, chatRoomId, }

ChatMessage ChatMessage { _id, bookingId, fromUserId, toUserId, text, media: [url], timestamp, seen: Boolean }

Admin / Audit VerificationRequest { providerId, documents, submittedAt, reviewedBy, reviewedAt, decision } Report { reporterId, targetId (user/provider), bookingId, reason, status }

âœ… 3) API Endpoints (high-level, routes + purpose) Auth

POST /api/auth/send-otp â€” send OTP via Firebase (body: phone, role)

POST /api/auth/verify-otp â€” verify OTP -> returns JWT + user profile

POST /api/auth/register-provider â€” initial provider registration (basic info)

Users

GET /api/users/me â€” profile

PUT /api/users/me â€” update profile, add address

Providers

POST /api/providers/onboard â€” upload documents, skills

GET /api/providers/nearby?lat=&lng=&cat=Plumber â€” list nearby available providers (returns providers in area, distance)

GET /api/providers/:id â€” provider public profile + reviews

Bookings

POST /api/bookings â€” create booking request

GET /api/bookings/:id â€” booking details

GET /api/bookings/user â€” bookings for logged-in user

GET /api/bookings/provider â€” bookings for logged-in provider

PUT /api/bookings/:id/assign â€” admin/provider assign

PUT /api/bookings/:id/status â€” update (accept, start, complete, cancel)

POST /api/bookings/:id/price-quote â€” provider sends quote

Chat

GET /api/chat/:bookingId/history

POST /api/chat/:bookingId/message â€” text/media (upload via Cloudinary)

Admin

GET /api/admin/providers/pending â€” list of pending verifications

PUT /api/admin/providers/:id/verify â€” approve/reject

GET /api/admin/stats â€” basic analytics

âœ… 4) Key flows (textual) â€” 3 main flows Flow A â€” User books a plumber

User login via OTP â†’ select category â€œPlumberâ€ â†’ fill problem (text + photo) â†’ choose address + preferred time â†’ Submit booking.

Backend stores booking with status requested. System finds providers in area and pushes request to their dashboard queue (Socket.IO / notification).

Provider gets a request (can accept/reject). If accepted â†’ status assigned and user notified and chat room created.

Provider arrives â†’ marks in_progress â†’ completes â†’ marks completed. Payment via COD or online. Rating prompt shown.

Flow B â€” Provider onboarding & verification

Provider registers (phone OTP), fills details, uploads Aadhar/PAN/DL.

Admin reviews verification via admin panel, can approve/reject. On approval provider verified=true and visible to users.

Flow C â€” Chat between user & provider (for booking)

Socket.IO room keyed by bookingId. Messages saved to ChatMessage collection. Uploads via Cloudinary signed upload, then send URL.

âœ… 5) Frontend UI wireframe + components (quick) Key pages & components

Splash / RoleSelect: big CTA buttons (User / Provider)

Home (User): Search bar, categories cards, â€œNearby providersâ€ list, map toggle

BookForm: select category â†’ describe problem â†’ add photos â†’ choose slot â†’ confirm

Provider profile: rating, services, priceRange, verification badge

BookingList: upcoming + past bookings with status chips

Chat: message list + input + attachment button

Provider Dashboard: incoming requests queue, calendar, earnings card, accept/reject buttons

Admin Panel: table of provider verification requests, stats cards

UI notes: Use Poppins font, rounded cards, glassy buttons. Dark/light toggle optional. Mobile-first.

